The paper deals with the state complexity of languages, which is a topic in formal language theory (cs.FL). It also involves combinatorics (cs.DM) and complexity theory (cs.CC). The use of Dedekind numbers and onto functions suggests a connection to information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the paper involves some mathematical logic (cs.LO) in the form of automata theory.
